    {{Infobox keyword | type = Activated | first = Kaladesh | last = Modern Horizons 3 | N = N | reminder = Tap any number of other untapped creatures you control with total power N or greater: This permanent becomes an artifact creature until end of turn. | stats= {{stats|W=5|U=8|B=3|R=5|G=5|WU=2|UR=1|RW=1|A=54}} }} '''Crew''' is a [[keyword ability]] introduced in ''[[Kaladesh]]'' to enable the [[vehicle]] artifact subtype. It allows vehicles to become [[artifact creatures]] until end of turn.{{DailyRef|feature/kaladesh-mechanics-2016-09-02|''Kaladesh'' Mechanics|[[Matt Tabak]]|September 2, 2016}}

    ==Description== To [[activate]] the crew ability, tap any number of [[creatures]] you control with total power equal to or greater than the crew number. Because the crew ability doesn't use the [[tap symbol]], you can tap any untapped creature you control, even one that just entered the battlefield. You can even tap an animated Vehicle to crew a Vehicle. Crew evolved from a "location" mechanic, originally envisioned for ''[[Ixalan]]''.{{DailyRef|card-preview/conquering-design-ixalan-2017-09-05|Conquering the Design of ''Ixalan''|[[Ken Nagle]]|September 5, 2017}} The mechanic was first previewed on the card Ovalchase Dragster at [[PAX|Pax West]] [[2016]].[https://www.twitch.tv/magic/profile Magic Twitch channel] (September 2, 2016). [https://www.twitch.tv/magic/v/87178950 Magic at PAX: Kaladesh Debut].

    ===History=== After ''Kaladesh'' crew also appeared in ''[[Aether Revolt]]''.{{DailyRef|making-magic/revolting-development-and-design-part-1-2017-01-02|A Revolting Development (and Design), Part 1|[[Mark Rosewater]]|January 2, 2017}}{{DailyRef|feature/aether-revolt-mechanics-2017-01-02|''Aether Revolt'' Mechanics|[[Matt Tabak]]|January 2, 2017}} and ''[[Ixalan]]''{{DailyRef|feature/ixalan-mechanics|''Ixalan'' Mechanics|[[Matt Tabak]]|August 28, 2017}} which made the mechanic ''Crew'' available in two different non-neighbouring blocks in [[Standard]]. It was also used for the [[Skyship Weatherlight|''Weatherlight'']] in ''[[Dominaria]]''.{{DailyRef|making-magic/returning-home-2018-04-02|Returning Home|[[Mark Rosewater]]|Mark Rosewater}} The mechanic is now considered to be in the low end of [[evergreen]] or the high end of [[deciduous]].{{EzTumblr|https://markrosewater.tumblr.com/post/189946097658/since-when-did-crew-become-evergreen-your|title=Since when did Crew become evergreen?|December 29, 2019}} While [[Pilot|Pilots]] regularly modify the Vehicles they Crew, {{Card|Mindlink Mech}} and {{Card|Getaway Car}} are the first Vehicles to interact with the creatures that Crew them.

    ===Rules change=== Previously, a vehicle that had become a creature was able to be tapped for its ''own'' crew ability. This rarely came up, and it doesn't make a lot of sense for a vehicle to crew itself, so the rules were changed slightly to prevent that. Starting with ''[[Kamigawa: Neon Dynasty]]'', you must now tap ''another'' creature to crew a vehicle.

